5: So, you want us to watch over him?
8:
Indeed. Excuse the short notice—our
usual babysitter is busy at the
moment, so we reluctantly decided
to hire a few adventurers.
10:
Um, hello... My name is Toran.
Pleased to meet you.
13:
Hello to you too, Toran. 
It'll only be a short while, 
but we'll take care of you.
16:
Hm... I presumed all adventurers
were of the uncouth sort, but
perhaps I was mistaken.
18:
Toran is my pride and joy. 
My late wife would never forgive me, 
were something to happen to him.
22:
Leave him to us! We'll take good
care of him!
28:
That answer's correct, this one too...
Wow, these are all correct.
32:
Wow! That's amazing, Toran! You
got perfect scores!
38:
It's nothing, really. I must study hard
if I want to take over my father's
business!
41:
But Toran, your Oudo—I mean, you
seem like you're being hard on
yourself. Are you sure you don't
wanna play?
47:
All work and no play will make you
dull, Toran. Children are meant to
play and have fun.
51:
Besides, we already finished our
schoolwork for today. I don't see any
harm in having a little fun.
54:
W-well, then... Okay. I would like to
play outside!
57:
Great! Come on everyone, let's go
outside!
63:
Oh, over there! That shop is known
for having great imports! And that
stall—apparently they're having
trouble securing inventory!
66:
Wow, Toran! You sure know a lot
about these shops!
69:
Heh-heh! Of course. One day, I'm
going to become a great merchant,
just like my father!
72:
I... see... It's almost as though you're
conducting market research. Is this...
what children do for fun nowadays?
76:
Don't worry, Toran is having lots of
fun right now. I can tell.
79:
But... I can tell that he's interested in
something else, too.
87:
Y-yes, I would like to try playing tag,
or perhaps tossing a ball around...
But, I've never really tried it before.
89:
Our attendants never really seem
interested in playing... and I don't
have any friends...
100:
Heehee! You're so good at this,
Toran! Maybe you can be an athlete
someday?
103:
Huh. I haven't seen you 'round here
before. Coulda swore I knew
everyone in this neighborhood...
105: Eh, whatever. Wanna play with us?
111: Go on, Toran. Go play with them.
118:
Toran's lying... You do want to play
with them, don't you?
121:
I... I can't. Father says that I'm not
allowed to play with the children
around here.
123:
Father says... the children around
here, they're all commoners...
129:
You must love your father very
much. I can sense it in your Oudo.
138:
...I'm still trying to understand
humans. So, I don't know if this will
help, but...
142:
Your father is your father. And you
are you.
145:
Tell me, Toran... How do you really
feel?
150:
...If my father gets mad at me...
could you be there to apologize with
me?
153:
No problem, heehee! Lady Memram
always gets mad at me, so I'm used
to it!
156:
H-hey! Sorry about earlier... Could I,
maybe, join you guys?
163:
I will ask again. What, EXACTLY, was
it that you were THINKING?!
167:
U-umm, well... After we played with
Toran, I went to go talk to his father...
170:
And I tried sooo hard, so that Toran
and his father would understand
each other. And then—
173:
Lady Memram, was it? 
Please, place no blame on Miss Elmor.
175:
Miss Elmor managed to soothe my
heart, which had been broken ever
since the passing of my late wife.
177:
Not only this, but she even mended
the relationship between my dear
son and me. I truly cannot thank her
enough!
185:
I don't understand it either. It just...
happened, I guess?
189:
I'm still learning about humans! 
I'm bound to make some mistakes, 
right?
192:
You can always keep learning. 
And if it's to support Miss Elmor, 
I do not mind parting with some of 
my finances, either.
194:
Same goes for us! The Elmor
Fanclub will support you all the way!
197:
Hero of the Red Soup! 
Did I not leave her in your care?
201:
Wha—?! I didn't expect this to
happen either!
205:
Don't worry, we still have plenty of
time to get to know each other!
